    in_dialogue_with: "This concept enters into an active, fruitful dialogue with epistemology of testimony in Western philosophy. While epistemology of testimony in Western philosophy often seeks to analyze truth through a specific, structured lens, Shabda Pramana expands this view by highlighting the relational, intuitive, or contextual dimensions of understanding. This comparison reveals that different traditions often converge on the same fundamental problems of existence, using different vocabularies to express a shared human search for meaning.",
    critique: "The primary criticism leveled against Shabda Pramana within the historical debates of the tradition is that it can easily slide into blind obedience and intellectual dogmatism. Opponents argue that by emphasizing this perspective, the philosophy struggles to justify a stable, objective foundation for empirical science and social laws. To address this critique, subsequent thinkers in the Nyaya school had to develop complex theories of dual-level truth, showing how the ultimate and relative dimensions of reality can be harmonized without contradiction.",
